WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.675 --> 00:00:11.885
REESE: When you find that one person
who connects you to the world...

2
00:00:12.804 --> 00:00:15.514
...you become someone different.

3
00:00:16.349 --> 00:00:18.934
Someone better.

4
00:00:21.229 --> 00:00:23.939
When that person is taken from you...

5
00:00:26.735 --> 00:00:28.902
...what do you become then?

6
00:00:36.202 --> 00:00:38.245
MAN:
Whatever you wanna do. you know? Unh.

7
00:00:39.539 --> 00:00:40.706
What? Hmm?

8
00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:45.919
What. where did you get that. in a cereal
box? Huh? You wanna see a real gun?

9
00:00:47.255 --> 00:00:48.505
Forget you.

10
00:00:48.715 --> 00:00:52.426
Every punk is carrying. That's why your
father wanted us to take the car home.

11
00:00:52.635 --> 00:00:54.553
Relax.

12
00:00:54.763 --> 00:00:58.432
Picking up new hardware next week.
Restore a little order.

13
00:00:59.434 --> 00:01:02.936
Besides. when we take the car.
we don't get to meet new friends.

14
00:01:03.146 --> 00:01:04.271
Like this guy.

15
00:01:04.814 --> 00:01:06.440
[CHUCKLES]

16
00:01:18.244 --> 00:01:20.621
You bring enough
for the whole group?

17
00:01:21.623 --> 00:01:24.249
Time to teach you about sharing.

18
00:01:31.549 --> 00:01:32.674
[ALL GRUNTING]

19
00:01:42.977 --> 00:01:45.229
[ANTON COUGHING]

20
00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:51.485
[CHATTERING ON MONITOR]

21
00:02:03.039 --> 00:02:06.500
I'll need a statement from the bum.
Which hospital did they take him to?

22
00:02:06.709 --> 00:02:09.878
Declined treatment.
We got video on it though.

23
00:02:28.356 --> 00:02:30.983
You know.
you could've done me a favor...

24
00:02:31.192 --> 00:02:34.194
...and let those guys
land a couple more punches.

25
00:02:34.404 --> 00:02:36.446
Question for you.

26
00:02:36.948 --> 00:02:41.034
Looking at that tape. I'd say
you spent some time in the service.

27
00:02:42.120 --> 00:02:43.704
I did.

28
00:02:44.330 --> 00:02:45.747
Army.

29
00:02:45.957 --> 00:02:48.041
Two tours in Iraq.

30
00:02:48.251 --> 00:02:51.503
But you don't learn how to fight like that
in the regular army.

31
00:02:51.838 --> 00:02:55.674
So. what were you?
Special Forces? Delta?

32
00:02:58.678 --> 00:03:01.513
I'm Carter. You didn't give us a name.

33
00:03:03.683 --> 00:03:06.476
You know. it's funny.
Best parts of your life...

34
00:03:07.061 --> 00:03:09.021
...you don't need a name.

35
00:03:09.522 --> 00:03:12.608
You get to be "Dad."
"sweetheart." "pal."

36
00:03:13.276 --> 00:03:17.279
Seems like the only time you need
a name now is when you're in trouble.

37
00:03:18.156 --> 00:03:19.865
So am I in trouble?

38
00:03:20.408 --> 00:03:22.576
I don't know. You tell me.

39
00:03:22.785 --> 00:03:24.661
You're the one living on the street.

40
00:03:27.498 --> 00:03:31.251
You're not from here. are you?
What. you're just passing through?

41
00:03:32.629 --> 00:03:35.047
I came to find an old friend.

44
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:47.684
That disconnect between
what they were trained to do...

45
00:03:47.977 --> 00:03:50.896
...and what they were expected to do
when they got home.

46
00:03:51.105 --> 00:03:54.441
Some of them just
needed a little help adjusting.

47
00:03:57.612 --> 00:03:59.905
You need some help?

48
00:04:05.453 --> 00:04:07.913
Of course. some other guys I knew...

49
00:04:09.082 --> 00:04:11.208
...they had done so many evil things...

50
00:04:11.417 --> 00:04:14.753
...they felt
like they needed the punishment.

51
00:04:17.340 --> 00:04:19.508
That sound more like your story. "pal"?

52
00:04:23.429 --> 00:04:25.264
Excuse me for a second.

53
00:04:42.073 --> 00:04:43.865
ATTORNEY:
I'm here for my client.

54
00:04:44.867 --> 00:04:47.911
TECH:
Wow. Wow. wow.

55
00:04:48.121 --> 00:04:51.581
Your guy's prints were found in half
a dozen crime scenes over the years.

56
00:04:51.791 --> 00:04:53.875
Open warrants
in four different countries.

57
00:04:54.085 --> 00:04:57.713
Missing Persons here in Queens.
'07. three guys disappeared.

58
00:04:57.922 --> 00:05:01.591
Who you got down there. Carter?
The angel of death?

59
00:05:02.844 --> 00:05:05.304
I appreciate the help. counselor.

60
00:05:05.513 --> 00:05:09.182
But who's picking up the tab?

61
00:05:11.894 --> 00:05:14.396
Our employer
wants to have a word with you.

62
00:05:30.538 --> 00:05:31.788
[ENGINE STARTS]

63
00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:36.043
[CHATTERING ON MONITOR]

64
00:05:55.229 --> 00:05:57.272
Do I owe you money?

65
00:05:57.482 --> 00:06:01.401
Because I'm. uh. running a little short
at the moment.

66
00:06:01.611 --> 00:06:04.529
FINCH:
You don't owe me anything. Mr. Reese.

67
00:06:05.365 --> 00:06:07.491
That's the name you prefer. isn't it?

68
00:06:07.700 --> 00:06:09.951
I know you've had several.

69
00:06:11.287 --> 00:06:14.581
Don't worry.
I'm not gonna tell anybody about you.

70
00:06:15.833 --> 00:06:18.585
You don't know anything about me.

71
00:06:18.795 --> 00:06:22.464
I know exactly everything about you.
Mr. Reese.

72
00:06:22.673 --> 00:06:25.842
I know about the work you used to do
for the government.

73
00:06:26.052 --> 00:06:29.096
I know about the doubts
you came to have about that work.

74
00:06:29.305 --> 00:06:33.016
I know that the government. along
with everybody else. thinks you're dead.

75
00:06:35.228 --> 00:06:39.064
I know you've spent the last couple of
months trying to drink yourself to death.

76
00:06:40.483 --> 00:06:43.944
I know you're contemplating
more efficient ways to do it.

77
00:06:45.154 --> 00:06:46.279
Which would be a shame.

78
00:06:47.865 --> 00:06:50.700
So you see.
knowledge is not my problem.

79
00:06:51.369 --> 00:06:54.204
Doing something
with that knowledge...

80
00:06:54.914 --> 00:06:57.249
...that's where you'd come in.

81
00:06:58.709 --> 00:06:59.751
Who sent you?

82
00:06:59.961 --> 00:07:02.003
Nobody sent me.

83
00:07:02.213 --> 00:07:04.589
You can call me Mr. Finch.

84
00:07:06.926 --> 00:07:09.719
I think you and I
can help one another.

85
00:07:10.763 --> 00:07:14.641
I don't think you need a psychiatrist
or a support group or pills.

86
00:07:16.102 --> 00:07:17.269
What do I need?

87
00:07:17.478 --> 00:07:19.771
You need a purpose.

88
00:07:21.441 --> 00:07:24.151
More specifically. you need a job.

89
00:07:30.283 --> 00:07:32.617
FINCH:
Eight million people.

90
00:07:33.536 --> 00:07:35.454
You know what they all have
in common?

91
00:07:36.789 --> 00:07:39.791
None of them knows
what happens next.

92
00:07:40.042 --> 00:07:41.585
Good things. maybe.

93
00:07:41.794 --> 00:07:43.420
But for some of them. not so good.

94
00:07:44.797 --> 00:07:49.092
Someone is murdered in New York City
every 18 hours. It's like Musical Chairs.

95
00:07:49.302 --> 00:07:52.012
At the end of the day.
one of these people will be gone.

96
00:07:52.638 --> 00:07:55.474
Bad things happen to people
every day.

97
00:07:55.683 --> 00:07:59.102
- You can't stop that.
- What if you could?

98
00:07:59.312 --> 00:08:01.521
Not things that happen
in the heat of the moment.

99
00:08:01.731 --> 00:08:07.486
But so many crimes are planned
days. weeks in advance.

100
00:08:07.695 --> 00:08:10.614
What if you could stop those?

101
00:08:11.157 --> 00:08:12.449
Let me guess...

102
00:08:12.658 --> 00:08:14.075
...you're a psychic.

103
00:08:14.535 --> 00:08:17.662
Ha. ha. No psychic. no magic.
None of that.

104
00:08:17.872 --> 00:08:19.289
It's funny. when I was a kid...

105
00:08:19.499 --> 00:08:23.752
...I wanted a jet pack.
I wanted a summer house on Mars.

106
00:08:23.961 --> 00:08:27.005
Then I realized I was living in
the Information Age.

107
00:08:27.215 --> 00:08:29.633
This was a shocking disappointment
to me...

108
00:08:29.842 --> 00:08:33.053
...until I realized
how revolutionary it was.

109
00:08:33.262 --> 00:08:38.350
All of us are leaving a trail
of information in our wake.

110
00:08:38.559 --> 00:08:40.977
Most of it's useless.

111
00:08:42.021 --> 00:08:44.397
There's something hidden
in all that mess.

112
00:08:44.690 --> 00:08:47.359
A faint outline of things to come.

113
00:08:48.027 --> 00:08:51.488
The right person in the right place
with the right information...

114
00:08:51.697 --> 00:08:54.115
...could change everything.

115
00:08:55.201 --> 00:08:57.160
This is the problem I have. Mr. Reese...

116
00:08:57.370 --> 00:08:59.454
...I've got a list.

117
00:08:59.664 --> 00:09:03.667
A list of people who are about
to be involved in very bad situations.

118
00:09:03.876 --> 00:09:05.877
Murders. kidnappings.

119
00:09:06.087 --> 00:09:09.881
- Where did you get this list?
- Can't tell you. you'll have to trust me.

120
00:09:10.091 --> 00:09:14.636
The people that are on my list. they have
no idea that anything's about to happen.

121
00:09:14.845 --> 00:09:17.764
Most of them are just ordinary people.

122
00:09:19.016 --> 00:09:20.350
Like who?

123
00:09:21.310 --> 00:09:23.186
- Like her.
- Thank you.

124
00:09:25.189 --> 00:09:27.315
FINCH:
Her name is Diane Hansen.

125
00:09:27.525 --> 00:09:30.110
And this week.
she's at the top of my list.

126
00:09:30.319 --> 00:09:32.696
Think something bad
is gonna happen involving her?

127
00:09:33.030 --> 00:09:34.155
FINCH:
It's not that simple.

128
00:09:34.365 --> 00:09:37.993
I don't know exactly what's gonna
happen or what her role in it is.

129
00:09:38.995 --> 00:09:41.496
She might be the victim.
She could be the perpetrator.

130
00:09:41.706 --> 00:09:43.915
All I know is that she is involved.

131
00:09:44.125 --> 00:09:47.335
I want you to follow her.
Figure out what's gonna happen.

132
00:09:47.545 --> 00:09:49.087
And stop it from happening.

133
00:09:49.380 --> 00:09:50.672
Why not call the police?

134
00:09:51.966 --> 00:09:54.926
If anybody knew I had this list.
it would be...

135
00:09:55.136 --> 00:09:57.053
...problematic.

136
00:09:57.888 --> 00:10:01.850
You would name your own salary.
expenses. whatever you need.

137
00:10:02.059 --> 00:10:04.019
So. what do you think?

138
00:10:07.857 --> 00:10:09.983
I think you're a bored rich guy.

139
00:10:10.192 --> 00:10:13.820
I think that woman's your ex-wife
or someone you rode in an elevator with.

140
00:10:14.030 --> 00:10:15.905
Either way. I think I'm done.

141
00:10:20.870 --> 00:10:22.412
[GUARDS GRUNT]

142
00:10:29.378 --> 00:10:30.962
[CHATTERING ON MONITOR]

143
00:10:34.884 --> 00:10:38.303
WOMAN [ON TV]: Police are looking for
a homeless man for further questioning.

144
00:10:38.512 --> 00:10:40.680
The unidentified man
was originally believed...

145
00:10:40.890 --> 00:10:43.642
...to be the victim
of a violent assault on a subway.

146
00:10:43.851 --> 00:10:46.478
But now police consider the man
a person of interest...

147
00:10:46.687 --> 00:10:49.522
...in a number of crimes nationwide.

148
00:10:49.732 --> 00:10:51.358
[MEN GRUNTING ON TV]

149
00:11:05.831 --> 00:11:08.166
REESE:
Hey. sweetheart. what's wrong?

150
00:11:08.376 --> 00:11:10.835
Jessica. what's wrong?

151
00:11:11.045 --> 00:11:12.629
[PHONE RINGING]

152
00:11:18.678 --> 00:11:20.303
[GRUNTING]

153
00:11:22.598 --> 00:11:24.516
[PHONE CONTINUES RINGING]

154
00:11:27.812 --> 00:11:29.938
FINCH [OVER PHONE]:
You need to understand. Mr. Reese.

155
00:11:30.147 --> 00:11:32.982
The information I have is incomplete.
But it's never wrong.

156
00:11:33.192 --> 00:11:35.694
You need to know
what it would be like to be forced...

157
00:11:35.903 --> 00:11:39.030
...to listen to someone get murdered
and not be able to do anything about it.

158
00:11:39.240 --> 00:11:40.740
[LINE CLICKS]

159
00:11:44.120 --> 00:11:45.495
[WOMAN SCREAMING THROUGH WALL]

160
00:11:46.247 --> 00:11:47.706
MAN 1:
Shut up!

161
00:11:47.915 --> 00:11:48.957
[BANGING]

162
00:11:50.584 --> 00:11:51.918
WOMAN:
Rick. no!

163
00:11:54.964 --> 00:11:56.214
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

164
00:12:03.639 --> 00:12:05.181
[WOMAN GROANS ON RECORDING]

165
00:12:05.391 --> 00:12:09.185
MAN 2 [ON RECORDING]:
Kill 138.7. X-ray.

166
00:12:09.395 --> 00:12:13.606
Twelve. August. 2008. 1:37 a.m.

167
00:12:14.734 --> 00:12:16.735
Too late.

168
00:12:16.944 --> 00:12:19.571
This recording is three years old.

169
00:12:19.780 --> 00:12:23.742
A woman murdered in this room
by her husband.

170
00:12:24.702 --> 00:12:26.619
For the insurance.

171
00:12:27.121 --> 00:12:29.164
You were too late for her.

172
00:12:29.373 --> 00:12:32.250
Just like you were too late
for your friend Jessica.

173
00:12:32.460 --> 00:12:35.962
You were halfway around the world
when she was killed.

174
00:12:36.797 --> 00:12:39.257
- What the hell do you know about it?
- It's the truth.

175
00:12:39.467 --> 00:12:42.177
You left the government
because they lied. I never will.

176
00:12:43.012 --> 00:12:45.263
A man with your skills
could make a lot of money...

177
00:12:45.473 --> 00:12:47.432
...in this world but you don't do it.

178
00:12:47.641 --> 00:12:50.977
I think all you ever wanted to do
is protect people.

179
00:13:03.073 --> 00:13:05.408
That's a wiretap recording.

180
00:13:06.368 --> 00:13:09.412
NSA or FISA. Government.

181
00:13:12.792 --> 00:13:15.919
- But you're not government.
- No. I'm not.

182
00:13:23.093 --> 00:13:27.722
I guess you could call me
a concerned third party.

183
00:13:29.308 --> 00:13:31.726
You couldn't have saved this woman.

184
00:13:31.936 --> 00:13:33.603
Or your friend.

185
00:13:33.813 --> 00:13:36.397
But you could have
if you had known in time.

186
00:13:36.607 --> 00:13:40.527
That's the other thing I'm offering you.
A chance to be there in time.

187
00:13:45.950 --> 00:13:47.784
It's not too late for her.

188
00:13:47.993 --> 00:13:50.203
You could help me stop
what's about to happen.

189
00:13:50.412 --> 00:13:52.413
The question is. will you?

190
00:14:15.896 --> 00:14:18.022
Diane Hansen.

191
00:14:18.566 --> 00:14:21.025
Grew up in Detroit.

192
00:14:21.235 --> 00:14:23.361
Moved to the city after law school.

193
00:14:23.571 --> 00:14:25.488
Single.

194
00:14:26.115 --> 00:14:29.367
- Does she have any enemies?
FINCH: One or two.

195
00:14:29.577 --> 00:14:31.578
She's an assistant district attorney.

196
00:14:31.787 --> 00:14:33.872
The best conviction record
in her department.

197
00:14:34.081 --> 00:14:38.084
Great. Nice short list
of possible suspects.

198
00:14:38.752 --> 00:14:41.421
We have no idea when this bad thing
might happen. huh?

199
00:14:41.630 --> 00:14:43.965
Could be in a week.
could be five minutes.

200
00:14:44.174 --> 00:14:47.510
That's why we need to learn
as much as we can about her.

201
00:14:48.262 --> 00:14:51.723
- How do you intend to begin?
- The slow way.

202
00:14:51.932 --> 00:14:53.099
Cultivate a relationship.

203
00:14:54.101 --> 00:14:58.688
Engineering situations
over weeks. months...

204
00:14:58.898 --> 00:15:01.107
...to allow you to earn the asset's trust.

205
00:15:01.483 --> 00:15:02.984
FINCH:
And the fast way?

206
00:15:05.279 --> 00:15:09.073
Break into her home
and go through all her stuff.

207
00:16:00.501 --> 00:16:01.834
REESE:
What is this place?

208
00:16:02.044 --> 00:16:05.004
FINCH:
The decline of Western civilization.

209
00:16:05.214 --> 00:16:07.632
The city closed half its libraries.

210
00:16:07.841 --> 00:16:09.008
Budget cuts.

211
00:16:10.386 --> 00:16:13.888
This building was sold
to a bank that I control...

212
00:16:14.098 --> 00:16:16.349
...which promptly
declared bankruptcy.

213
00:16:18.185 --> 00:16:23.106
So the property is in a kind of limbo.
It doesn't exist.

214
00:16:23.315 --> 00:16:26.484
REESE: Neither do you.
I did a little digging.

215
00:16:26.694 --> 00:16:29.487
I recognize. Mr. Reese.
that there is a disparity...

216
00:16:29.697 --> 00:16:33.783
...between how much I know about you
and how much you know about me.

217
00:16:33.993 --> 00:16:37.120
I know you'll be trying to close that gap
as quickly as possible.

218
00:16:37.329 --> 00:16:42.208
But I should tell you
I'm a really private person.

219
00:16:44.253 --> 00:16:47.338
What have you found out about
our Ms. Hansen?

220
00:16:47.548 --> 00:16:48.840
Well. she's squeaky-clean.

221
00:16:49.049 --> 00:16:51.134
No debts. no attachments.

222
00:16:51.343 --> 00:16:55.179
But she is taking ulcer medication.
sleeping pills...

223
00:16:55.389 --> 00:16:57.932
...so she's scared or stressed
about something.

224
00:16:58.142 --> 00:17:01.019
Assuming she's the target.
I'm going through her work e-mails...

225
00:17:01.228 --> 00:17:04.230
...case files. looking for
anyone who stands out.

226
00:17:05.733 --> 00:17:08.067
I've got picture on her.

227
00:17:10.112 --> 00:17:11.696
But I need sound.

228
00:17:11.905 --> 00:17:13.281
I could hack her cell phone...

229
00:17:13.490 --> 00:17:16.534
...use the microphone to listen in.
GPS to track her.

230
00:17:16.744 --> 00:17:19.162
But that takes gear
that's a little hard to come by.

231
00:17:19.788 --> 00:17:21.497
Thought you might need that.

232
00:17:21.707 --> 00:17:24.667
- So I built one.
- Oh.

233
00:17:30.424 --> 00:17:33.426
"Good with computers."

234
00:17:40.559 --> 00:17:42.268
Driver's licenses.

235
00:17:43.062 --> 00:17:46.856
Credit cards. Six cover identities.

236
00:17:47.483 --> 00:17:50.109
Funds to be replenished
through a proxy corporation.

237
00:17:50.903 --> 00:17:53.738
Just like when you were
with the agency.

238
00:17:54.948 --> 00:17:56.324
When I was with the agency...

239
00:17:57.576 --> 00:17:59.952
...I knew who was picking up the tab.

240
00:18:00.162 --> 00:18:02.246
This is your list?

241
00:18:02.456 --> 00:18:04.457
- The list?
- Yup.

242
00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:07.460
REESE:
But you don't get names. do you?

243
00:18:09.797 --> 00:18:11.589
These are Social Security numbers...

244
00:18:11.799 --> 00:18:15.718
...and each of them map out
to a violent crime.

245
00:18:16.595 --> 00:18:20.431
- And all of these numbers represent...
- Lost chances.

246
00:18:20.641 --> 00:18:24.310
I could be more help if you'd tell me
where you're getting these numbers.

247
00:18:24.520 --> 00:18:29.232
It doesn't matter where. What you need
to know is that the next number is hers.

248
00:18:29.858 --> 00:18:31.359
Trust works both ways. Finch.

249
00:18:31.568 --> 00:18:35.071
If telling me where you're getting these
numbers would put your life at risk...

250
00:18:35.280 --> 00:18:37.657
It would put a lot more people
than just me at risk.

251
00:18:38.075 --> 00:18:40.785
And I'd say trusting an alcoholic
ex-government hit man...

252
00:18:40.994 --> 00:18:44.163
...is a greater challenge
than trusting a middle-aged cripple.

253
00:18:44.373 --> 00:18:48.167
I have one more address
for you to check out tonight.

254
00:19:30.210 --> 00:19:31.502
[PHONE DIALING]

255
00:19:33.505 --> 00:19:35.173
Okay. Mr. Finch.

256
00:19:35.382 --> 00:19:38.301
- What am I doing here?
FINCH [OVER PHONE]: Sleeping.

257
00:19:38.510 --> 00:19:41.053
You have plenty to do tomorrow.

258
00:19:41.805 --> 00:19:43.222
What are you talking about?

259
00:19:44.099 --> 00:19:45.850
Who lives here?

260
00:19:46.059 --> 00:19:48.561
You do. Mr. Reese.

261
00:20:02.075 --> 00:20:03.492
Any luck finding Paul Bunyan?

262
00:20:03.702 --> 00:20:06.370
Turns out "bearded loner"
covers a high percentage...

263
00:20:06.580 --> 00:20:08.915
...of the homeless population.

264
00:20:09.833 --> 00:20:11.667
Oh. thanks.

265
00:20:12.002 --> 00:20:15.338
Wait. is this
the Missing Persons file from '07?

266
00:20:15.547 --> 00:20:17.215
MAN: Yes. ma'am.
- This is all they had?

267
00:20:17.424 --> 00:20:18.633
MAN:
Yep.

268
00:20:31.730 --> 00:20:34.023
REESE: Given Hansen's job.
we've got hundreds of people...

269
00:20:34.233 --> 00:20:35.816
...who could be holding a grudge...

270
00:20:36.026 --> 00:20:41.113
...so I'm starting with the people she's
worried about. I cut the list to three.

271
00:20:41.323 --> 00:20:44.909
The first is Lawrence Pope.
the man Hansen is currently prosecuting.

272
00:20:45.118 --> 00:20:48.246
FUSCO: When we got there.
the scene was. uh. colorful.

273
00:20:48.455 --> 00:20:49.747
Five dead.

274
00:20:49.957 --> 00:20:53.292
One of them had managed to crawl
10 feet to a phone to dial 911...

275
00:20:53.502 --> 00:20:57.088
...despite the fact that this drug-slinging
piece of trash shot him in the gut.

276
00:20:57.297 --> 00:20:59.966
- Your Honor.
- Pardon me. Your Honor.

277
00:21:00.300 --> 00:21:02.885
Despite the fact that this
drug-slinging piece of trash...

278
00:21:03.095 --> 00:21:05.012
...allegedly shot him in the gut.

279
00:21:05.222 --> 00:21:07.390
The person who made that call
was Germaine Salts.

280
00:21:07.599 --> 00:21:10.726
- And he was friends with the defendant?
FUSCO: Yeah. they were all friends.

281
00:21:10.936 --> 00:21:13.145
We figure that's how Pope knew
the deal was going down.

282
00:21:13.355 --> 00:21:15.898
Turns out career criminals
don't make trustworthy friends.

283
00:21:16.108 --> 00:21:18.567
Detective Fusco.
when you interviewed Mr. Pope...

284
00:21:18.777 --> 00:21:20.361
...what did he tell you in his defense?

285
00:21:20.570 --> 00:21:22.488
FUSCO:
He said if he'd shot the poor bastard...

286
00:21:22.698 --> 00:21:27.618
...he would've shot him in the head.
quote. "Same as I always do." unquote.

287
00:21:27.828 --> 00:21:31.455
Said he wouldn't have left him there
half dead. blubbering for his girlfriend.

288
00:21:35.502 --> 00:21:37.670
No more questions. Your Honor.

289
00:21:47.723 --> 00:21:49.056
HANSEN [OVER RADIO]:
Detective...

290
00:21:49.266 --> 00:21:51.517
...you went a little off script
in your testimony.

291
00:21:52.144 --> 00:21:54.103
You never told me
about that conversation...

292
00:21:54.313 --> 00:21:56.230
...and it could clear Pope's name.

293
00:21:56.857 --> 00:21:58.774
What's it matter. we got the guy.

294
00:21:58.984 --> 00:22:01.277
It matters because
it's my job to make sure...

295
00:22:01.486 --> 00:22:04.280
...the wrong people don't go to jail.
Remember?

296
00:22:04.489 --> 00:22:06.657
Excuse me. I thought
we were on the same team.

297
00:22:11.038 --> 00:22:13.164
You got time to talk?
I could buy you dinner?

298
00:22:13.373 --> 00:22:15.666
- Busy. Another time?
- Is something wrong?

299
00:22:15.876 --> 00:22:18.878
- I've been noticing lately...
HANSEN: No. I'm fine. Thank you. Thanks.

300
00:22:20.922 --> 00:22:23.966
REESE: The second person I'm looking
into is Wheeler. her co-counselor.

301
00:22:24.176 --> 00:22:26.927
Another ADA? Why?

302
00:22:27.137 --> 00:22:29.555
Well. they dated
for a few months last year.

303
00:22:29.765 --> 00:22:32.058
She broke things off.
and 40% of murders...

304
00:22:32.267 --> 00:22:34.310
...involve some kind of
romantic relationship.

305
00:22:34.519 --> 00:22:39.482
Also. Wheeler's divorced. one kid.
alimony. upside-down on his condo...

306
00:22:40.067 --> 00:22:43.110
...career's stalled.
HANSEN: I asked. I can't get the time off.

307
00:22:43.320 --> 00:22:45.529
Yeah. it is. It is a tough job.

308
00:22:45.739 --> 00:22:48.908
But I can look out for myself.
you know that.

309
00:22:50.202 --> 00:22:53.954
Listen. Mom. I... I know you haven't
been cashing the checks.

310
00:22:54.748 --> 00:22:56.582
It's not charity. I'm your daughter.

311
00:22:56.792 --> 00:22:58.584
I know. I know you worry about me.

312
00:22:59.878 --> 00:23:01.837
I... I'm fine.

313
00:23:02.047 --> 00:23:03.964
There's a third person
you're looking into?

314
00:23:05.675 --> 00:23:07.551
Ex-convict named Charles Robinson.

315
00:23:07.761 --> 00:23:11.389
Hansen and Wheeler prosecuted him
three years back. armed robbery.

316
00:23:11.807 --> 00:23:14.392
Robinson wrote them love letters
from prison.

317
00:23:14.851 --> 00:23:17.937
He's the first one
I'm gonna be looking into.

318
00:23:18.146 --> 00:23:22.817
Robinson was released two months ago.
Hansen pulled his file last week.

319
00:23:37.165 --> 00:23:38.582
[DOOR UNLOCKS]

320
00:23:45.799 --> 00:23:47.466
Don't move.

321
00:23:47.801 --> 00:23:49.385
I don't have much...

322
00:23:49.594 --> 00:23:52.346
...but you're welcome to take
whatever you need.

323
00:23:53.306 --> 00:23:56.142
I've been where you've been.

324
00:24:00.605 --> 00:24:02.648
I don't think Robinson is our man.

325
00:24:02.858 --> 00:24:06.277
He burned through a box of highlighters
on his King James Bible...

326
00:24:06.486 --> 00:24:08.362
...none of it Old Testament.

327
00:24:08.572 --> 00:24:12.074
- None of it Revelations.
- Fine. One down.

328
00:24:12.284 --> 00:24:13.784
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

329
00:24:19.458 --> 00:24:20.499
Hansen's on the move.

330
00:24:20.709 --> 00:24:24.462
She's phoning county lockup.
arranging a meeting with Pope.

331
00:24:24.671 --> 00:24:26.672
Alone.

332
00:24:26.882 --> 00:24:28.799
Isn't my lawyer supposed
to be here?

333
00:24:29.009 --> 00:24:33.179
I can call him. but the reason I'm here is
I don't think you murdered those people.

334
00:24:33.930 --> 00:24:37.475
I think somebody else was in the house
when that 911 call was made.

335
00:24:37.684 --> 00:24:41.395
Somebody who told you what was said.
which means you weren't there.

336
00:24:41.605 --> 00:24:43.355
Is it somebody
you're trying to protect?

337
00:24:43.565 --> 00:24:45.691
POPE [OVER PHONE]:
You're gonna help me? Is that it?

338
00:24:46.026 --> 00:24:47.985
Where you from. Ohio?

339
00:24:48.195 --> 00:24:50.446
I met DA's before.
you do a couple years of this...

340
00:24:50.655 --> 00:24:53.199
...then try for a high-dollar job
at a law firm.

341
00:24:53.408 --> 00:24:55.326
What happened. you get left behind?

342
00:24:55.535 --> 00:24:57.828
I know a guy that'd put you to work
out on a corner.

343
00:24:58.038 --> 00:24:59.330
Oh.

344
00:24:59.539 --> 00:25:01.207
Close.

345
00:25:01.666 --> 00:25:04.919
I grew up in Michigan. Brightmoor.
You know where that is?

346
00:25:05.128 --> 00:25:07.922
I don't think you would've lasted
very long there. Lawrence.

347
00:25:08.131 --> 00:25:10.674
I know what it's like
to want to get out of a place...

348
00:25:10.884 --> 00:25:13.052
...so bad you'd be willing
to do almost anything.

349
00:25:13.261 --> 00:25:16.180
And that's why I know. if you're gonna
take the fall for this...

350
00:25:16.389 --> 00:25:17.890
...you must be very scared. Now...

351
00:25:18.099 --> 00:25:21.227
...the person who knows what happened
must be somebody you care about.

352
00:25:21.436 --> 00:25:23.604
Is it your younger brother Michael?

353
00:25:23.813 --> 00:25:26.357
Pope's got a brother.
It's in his case file.

354
00:25:27.025 --> 00:25:28.984
- Got it.
- Did he see the real killers?

355
00:25:29.194 --> 00:25:32.112
You should leave this alone. lady.
I can do the time.

356
00:25:32.906 --> 00:25:36.909
Figure I'll make amends for all the things
you never caught me on. Because I'm bad.

357
00:25:37.452 --> 00:25:39.828
These people. they're evil.
Kill anyone they want.

358
00:25:40.038 --> 00:25:43.499
They're protected. Keep asking.
they'll kill me and my brother.

359
00:25:43.708 --> 00:25:46.752
- And probably you too.
- You can trust me.

360
00:25:46.962 --> 00:25:49.755
We'll take care of you
and your brother.

361
00:25:52.425 --> 00:25:56.887
If the killers are out there. I'm gonna
find them. It's my job. Now. why don't...?

362
00:25:57.097 --> 00:26:01.100
Bitch. you keep your damn mouth shut
or I'll shut it for you.

363
00:26:02.352 --> 00:26:03.519
[GASPING]

364
00:26:04.771 --> 00:26:05.980
[GRUNTING]

365
00:26:07.107 --> 00:26:08.190
I'm fine.

366
00:26:08.400 --> 00:26:09.858
Okay. She's okay. She's okay.

367
00:26:10.068 --> 00:26:12.069
Finch? You were right about Hansen.

368
00:26:12.279 --> 00:26:13.404
Whoever framed Pope...

369
00:26:13.613 --> 00:26:18.075
...will be coming after her. and only
Pope's brother knows who they are.

370
00:26:25.500 --> 00:26:27.209
[CHATTERING ON MONITOR]

371
00:26:27.794 --> 00:26:29.920
JESSICA [OVER PHONE]:
Hi. Mom. It's Jessica.

372
00:26:30.130 --> 00:26:33.674
I'm just down in Mexico with Cindy.
and I'll be back tomorrow.

373
00:26:33.883 --> 00:26:35.426
Okay? Talk soon. Bye.

374
00:26:35.635 --> 00:26:37.553
REESE: Cindy?
- Yeah.

375
00:26:38.179 --> 00:26:39.805
REESE: I look like a Cindy?
- Yeah.

376
00:26:40.807 --> 00:26:42.808
I didn't tell her about us yet.

377
00:26:43.852 --> 00:26:46.186
It's been six months.

378
00:26:46.396 --> 00:26:48.397
You haven't told your mom
you left your ex?

379
00:26:48.690 --> 00:26:52.276
Maybe you're starting to think
you got a bum deal...

380
00:26:52.485 --> 00:26:54.820
...trading an officer for an enlisted man.

381
00:26:55.780 --> 00:26:58.949
I wish this weekend
could go on forever.

382
00:27:01.494 --> 00:27:03.203
Already has.

383
00:27:03.705 --> 00:27:05.497
It's Tuesday.

384
00:27:05.707 --> 00:27:07.791
Which means you have to go back
to the base...

385
00:27:08.001 --> 00:27:11.128
...and I'm not gonna see you again
for two weeks. which I hate.

386
00:27:11.338 --> 00:27:13.297
Then ask me to stay.

387
00:27:13.506 --> 00:27:14.965
I will.

388
00:27:15.175 --> 00:27:18.927
I'll quit.

389
00:27:19.137 --> 00:27:21.930
- I'll quit.
- Okay. then quit.

390
00:27:22.682 --> 00:27:24.558
I already did.

391
00:27:24.768 --> 00:27:27.102
- What?
- Yeah.

392
00:27:28.730 --> 00:27:31.357
I didn't wanna take the chance...

393
00:27:31.858 --> 00:27:34.860
...that you wouldn't be here
when I got back.

394
00:27:35.945 --> 00:27:39.823
I've been training my whole life for
something that's never gonna happen.

395
00:27:41.576 --> 00:27:44.370
Everybody's too damn rich
to go to war.

396
00:27:45.538 --> 00:27:48.165
I'm obsolete and I love it.

397
00:27:48.375 --> 00:27:50.376
Because it means I get to be with you.

398
00:27:50.835 --> 00:27:53.629
I get my discharge in a month.

399
00:27:54.923 --> 00:27:57.049
Then I'm gonna buy a boat.

400
00:27:58.009 --> 00:28:00.886
And you get to be my first mate.

401
00:28:04.140 --> 00:28:06.892
But first we need some more tequila.

402
00:28:09.688 --> 00:28:11.855
[MAN SPEAKING IN SPANISH ON TV]

403
00:28:12.065 --> 00:28:13.357
[REESE CHUCKLING]

404
00:28:18.238 --> 00:28:20.572
Sweetheart. what's wrong? Jessica.

405
00:28:20.782 --> 00:28:22.408
What's wrong?

406
00:28:22.617 --> 00:28:25.244
Uh. it's New York. I don't know.
I don't know.

407
00:28:25.453 --> 00:28:27.496
Something happened this morning.

408
00:28:29.082 --> 00:28:33.210
- Is it a plane crash?
- I think it's two. I think it's two planes.

409
00:28:33.420 --> 00:28:35.421
[MAN CONTINUES SPEAKING
IN SPANISH ON TV]

410
00:28:39.175 --> 00:28:41.427
[CHATTERING ON MONITOR]

411
00:28:45.724 --> 00:28:47.307
HANSEN [OVER PHONE]:
Thanks.

412
00:28:48.685 --> 00:28:50.936
- You went to see Pope last night?
HANSEN: Yeah.

413
00:28:51.146 --> 00:28:54.231
I gave him one more chance
to turn in his accomplice. Cut a deal.

414
00:28:54.441 --> 00:28:56.775
- He give you anything?
HANSEN: No. as usual.

415
00:28:58.445 --> 00:29:00.696
I'm. uh... I'm late.

416
00:29:02.282 --> 00:29:04.491
REESE: She's trying to track down
Pope's brother.

417
00:29:04.701 --> 00:29:06.785
He can ID the real killers.

418
00:29:06.995 --> 00:29:09.288
And she's stonewalling Wheeler.

419
00:29:09.497 --> 00:29:11.623
What. does she think he's involved?

420
00:29:11.833 --> 00:29:15.586
Remember Pope said
they were protected from on high.

421
00:29:18.965 --> 00:29:20.299
REESE:
Wait a second.

422
00:29:22.969 --> 00:29:25.971
Turns out there's a good reason
she doesn't trust Wheeler.

423
00:29:26.181 --> 00:29:31.185
He might be working with the killers.
and they're after Michael Pope.

424
00:29:31.853 --> 00:29:34.855
We better get to this kid
before someone else does.

425
00:29:35.064 --> 00:29:36.440
[CHATTERING ON MONITOR]

426
00:29:37.400 --> 00:29:38.859
[BELL RINGS]

427
00:29:42.238 --> 00:29:43.489
[STUDENTS CHATTER]

428
00:29:49.913 --> 00:29:51.330
Michael?

429
00:29:51.539 --> 00:29:53.665
Can I talk to you for a second?

430
00:30:10.350 --> 00:30:12.893
- I got a message from your brother.
- You don't know him.

431
00:30:13.102 --> 00:30:16.313
Not exactly. I know what you saw.
I'm not the only one looking for you.

432
00:30:16.523 --> 00:30:17.773
You need to come with me.

433
00:30:20.193 --> 00:30:22.694
Hey. Hey. Help me.

434
00:30:22.904 --> 00:30:25.948
Hey. this man is trying
to put me into a taxicab with him.

435
00:30:26.157 --> 00:30:28.158
He's trying to take pictures of me.

436
00:30:29.202 --> 00:30:31.703
- What's going on?
- How you doing?

437
00:30:33.540 --> 00:30:35.499
- Michael Pope's still on the subway.
- Yeah.

438
00:30:35.708 --> 00:30:39.086
When he comes up for air you can use
the GPS on your phone to find him.

439
00:30:39.295 --> 00:30:43.674
If Pope's right about these guys.
I'm gonna need more than a cell phone.

440
00:30:43.883 --> 00:30:46.093
About that.
I don't like firearms very much.

441
00:30:46.302 --> 00:30:48.554
Neither do I.
But if someone has to have them...

442
00:30:48.763 --> 00:30:52.724
...I'd rather it was me. Besides. my friend
from the subway has a line on some.

443
00:30:54.185 --> 00:30:57.187
Lightly used. Steep discount.

444
00:30:57.939 --> 00:30:59.273
[RAP MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO]

445
00:30:59.482 --> 00:31:01.817
Let's roll. let's roll
Let's rock. let's rock

446
00:31:02.026 --> 00:31:03.318
Rock. roll
Rock. roll

447
00:31:03.528 --> 00:31:04.695
Hit the block
Hit the block

448
00:31:04.904 --> 00:31:07.364
Let's roll. let's roll
Let's rock. let's rock

449
00:31:10.743 --> 00:31:13.579
- Uh. what about this one?
- Are you planning on buying that one?

450
00:31:14.080 --> 00:31:16.123
- I'm just...
- Put it back on the table...

451
00:31:16.332 --> 00:31:18.917
...before somebody else
kicks your ass.

452
00:31:19.127 --> 00:31:21.753
REESE:
Have you guys seen the men's room?

453
00:31:22.714 --> 00:31:25.382
Hey. Anton. Good to see you again.

454
00:31:25.592 --> 00:31:27.593
You know this guy?

455
00:31:28.803 --> 00:31:31.054
Wow. that's some pretty serious
equipment.

456
00:31:31.264 --> 00:31:34.224
Have you guys taken a safety course?

457
00:31:35.101 --> 00:31:38.228
Take you. for instance.
You're holding that thing sideways.

458
00:31:38.438 --> 00:31:43.233
You can't aim it. and two. it'll eject
a shell casing right into your face. See?

459
00:31:50.033 --> 00:31:51.617
[ALL GRUNTING]

460
00:31:53.828 --> 00:31:56.038
[WOUNDED MEN GROANING]

461
00:32:02.045 --> 00:32:05.172
I'm gonna hold on to these
while you guys get some more practice.

462
00:32:06.007 --> 00:32:08.133
Have a nice day.

463
00:32:09.969 --> 00:32:11.637
Who the hell was that?

464
00:32:16.976 --> 00:32:18.810
All right. you're in.

465
00:32:23.024 --> 00:32:25.484
REESE: Wheeler's got a secret file
on Hansen. Finch.

466
00:32:26.569 --> 00:32:28.278
Old cases they worked together.

467
00:32:28.488 --> 00:32:31.615
Sounds interesting. Pictures please.

468
00:32:33.368 --> 00:32:35.702
Wait. wait. someone's coming.

469
00:32:42.293 --> 00:32:44.169
It's Hansen.

470
00:32:49.968 --> 00:32:52.636
Okay. now. You can go. Go. go. go.

471
00:33:05.191 --> 00:33:08.235
Reese? I got a signal from your phone.

472
00:33:09.320 --> 00:33:10.988
REESE:
Tell me you found Michael Pope.

473
00:33:11.197 --> 00:33:13.281
He's the only one
who knows who's after Hansen.

474
00:33:13.491 --> 00:33:17.160
I found him. but somebody else
found him first. Listen.

475
00:33:17.370 --> 00:33:22.833
Oh. Mikey. You were gonna tell him
all about us. weren't you? Hmm?

476
00:33:23.042 --> 00:33:24.960
- Head uptown.
- Are you hearing this?

477
00:33:28.006 --> 00:33:30.799
REESE:
97th and Riverside. Step on it.

478
00:33:31.467 --> 00:33:33.510
STILLS: Gonna put a couple
in the back of his head.

479
00:33:33.720 --> 00:33:35.762
Make it look like a gang thing.

480
00:33:36.389 --> 00:33:38.515
You gotta do something.

481
00:33:39.475 --> 00:33:40.559
REESE:
Relax.

482
00:33:42.562 --> 00:33:43.895
I'm on it.

483
00:33:44.147 --> 00:33:45.981
Keep the change.

484
00:34:14.510 --> 00:34:15.927
[GROANING]

485
00:34:16.971 --> 00:34:18.180
[GRUNTS]

486
00:34:25.897 --> 00:34:28.899
You're crazy. We're both dead now.

487
00:34:29.108 --> 00:34:32.110
- Do you know who they are?
- I do now.

488
00:34:33.571 --> 00:34:35.614
They're cops. Come on.

489
00:34:59.847 --> 00:35:02.140
REESE [ON MONITOR]:
What exactly have you gotten me into?

490
00:35:02.350 --> 00:35:04.643
FINCH [ON MONITOR]:
I don't know. That's the whole point.

491
00:35:04.852 --> 00:35:07.646
I hired you to help me figure that out.

492
00:35:09.565 --> 00:35:11.108
Here.

493
00:35:11.692 --> 00:35:14.152
I think we're up against
a group of corrupt cops.

494
00:35:14.403 --> 00:35:18.782
I think their next target is Hansen.
But I don't know for certain.

495
00:35:18.991 --> 00:35:20.283
I don't know anything...

496
00:35:20.493 --> 00:35:23.662
...because you won't tell me where
you're getting your information.

497
00:35:27.750 --> 00:35:31.670
When the towers came down.
you were in a hotel in Mexico.

498
00:35:32.922 --> 00:35:34.923
I was here.

499
00:35:35.550 --> 00:35:36.716
I was working.

500
00:35:36.926 --> 00:35:39.302
Didn't know about the attacks
until that evening.

501
00:35:40.138 --> 00:35:43.932
You see. Mr. Reese. until that day.
I had spent the better part of my life...

502
00:35:44.142 --> 00:35:45.642
...making myself very rich.

503
00:35:46.894 --> 00:35:49.938
Suddenly all that money
didn't seem to amount to much.

504
00:35:50.690 --> 00:35:52.440
Do you have a phone?

505
00:35:52.692 --> 00:35:54.526
Could you turn it off?

506
00:35:55.695 --> 00:35:57.237
Let's walk.

507
00:35:57.864 --> 00:36:00.991
Then I got a telephone call
from an old friend at the Pentagon.

508
00:36:01.367 --> 00:36:04.035
After the attacks
the government gave itself the power...

509
00:36:04.245 --> 00:36:08.665
...to read every e-mail.
listen to every cell phone.

510
00:36:08.875 --> 00:36:11.626
But they needed something
that could sort through it all.

511
00:36:11.836 --> 00:36:14.921
Something that could pick the terrorists
out of the population...

512
00:36:15.131 --> 00:36:16.548
...before they could act.

513
00:36:16.883 --> 00:36:17.924
They tried.

514
00:36:18.134 --> 00:36:20.969
Able Danger. SpiNNaker. TIA.

515
00:36:21.179 --> 00:36:22.512
But they were all failures.

516
00:36:22.722 --> 00:36:25.849
Well. their biggest failure was bad PR.

517
00:36:26.434 --> 00:36:28.852
The public wanted to be protected.

518
00:36:29.061 --> 00:36:31.396
They just didn't wanna know
how they were.

519
00:36:31.606 --> 00:36:36.401
So when they finally got a system
that worked. they kept it secret.

520
00:36:38.112 --> 00:36:40.322
So how do you know about it?

521
00:36:41.115 --> 00:36:42.991
I built it.

522
00:36:44.577 --> 00:36:47.913
"Good with computers." Remember?

523
00:36:51.417 --> 00:36:55.378
But there was a problem
with this machine.

524
00:36:55.588 --> 00:36:58.548
I had built it to prevent the next 9/11.

525
00:36:58.758 --> 00:37:02.802
But it was seeing all sorts of crimes.

526
00:37:03.012 --> 00:37:07.807
So I had to teach the machine
to divide the things it saw into two lists:

527
00:37:08.100 --> 00:37:11.478
Relevant and irrelevant.

528
00:37:11.687 --> 00:37:14.981
Events that would cause
massive loss of life were relevant.

529
00:37:15.191 --> 00:37:18.985
So those would be passed along
to the NSA or the FBI.

530
00:37:19.195 --> 00:37:21.321
REESE [ON MONITOR]:
And the irrelevant information?

531
00:37:23.699 --> 00:37:28.161
Every night. at midnight.
the machine erases it.

532
00:37:28.788 --> 00:37:32.123
It was only later
that I realized my mistake.

533
00:37:34.168 --> 00:37:38.880
The whole point of Pandora's Box.
once you open it. you can't close it.

534
00:37:39.966 --> 00:37:42.884
The idea of that irrelevant list...

535
00:37:43.302 --> 00:37:45.637
...was eating away at me.

536
00:37:45.846 --> 00:37:49.516
All those people with no idea
what was coming for them.

537
00:37:49.976 --> 00:37:52.227
So where is the machine now?

538
00:37:52.436 --> 00:37:54.187
What. the drives? Who knows?

539
00:37:54.397 --> 00:37:57.023
A government facility somewhere.

540
00:37:57.233 --> 00:37:58.483
But the machine?

541
00:38:00.319 --> 00:38:03.071
The machine is everywhere.

542
00:38:04.323 --> 00:38:07.492
Watching us with 10.000 eyes.

543
00:38:08.119 --> 00:38:10.829
Listening with a million ears.

544
00:38:11.038 --> 00:38:13.164
MAN: What did I tell you
about sending e-mails?

545
00:38:13.374 --> 00:38:15.000
WOMAN [ON MONITOR]:
You could move in.

546
00:38:15.209 --> 00:38:17.585
MAN: Never put anything in an e-mail
you cannot own.

547
00:38:17.795 --> 00:38:20.130
You gave yourself a way
to communicate with it?

548
00:38:20.339 --> 00:38:24.134
I was building the government
a tool of unimaginable power.

549
00:38:24.343 --> 00:38:27.721
I thought maybe an off switch
would come in handy.

550
00:38:28.014 --> 00:38:32.475
- So I built myself a backdoor into it.
- To access the irrelevant list.

551
00:38:32.977 --> 00:38:35.854
Just a Social Security number.

552
00:38:36.355 --> 00:38:39.482
If anyone ever found out.
I'd lose access. So nine digits.

553
00:38:39.692 --> 00:38:40.734
That's all we get.

554
00:38:40.943 --> 00:38:43.653
And we have no idea
why it picked Diane Hansen?

555
00:38:43.863 --> 00:38:47.657
It wouldn't be steering us toward her
if it wasn't seeing something.

556
00:38:47.867 --> 00:38:49.826
I don't know if I can protect Hansen.

557
00:38:50.036 --> 00:38:51.828
I can't see the whole picture.

558
00:38:55.833 --> 00:38:58.501
I offered you a job. Mr. Reese.

559
00:38:58.711 --> 00:39:01.171
Never said it would be easy.

560
00:39:06.552 --> 00:39:07.844
KANE: Hey. Carter.
- Yeah.

561
00:39:08.054 --> 00:39:10.680
KANE: You hear about your pal Anton?
- No.

562
00:39:10.890 --> 00:39:14.309
Him and his father tried to buy guns.
wound up getting shot.

563
00:39:14.518 --> 00:39:16.186
- Are they dead?
KANE: Nope. Embarrassed.

564
00:39:16.395 --> 00:39:19.898
They got taken out by one guy.
In a suit.

565
00:39:23.277 --> 00:39:24.944
[CHATTERING ON MONITOR]

566
00:39:38.918 --> 00:39:40.794
We've got all the parts.

567
00:39:41.003 --> 00:39:43.505
Question is.
how do they all fit together?

568
00:39:44.757 --> 00:39:48.176
Stills is narcotics.
Him and his men get word of deals.

569
00:39:48.511 --> 00:39:51.429
They steal the drugs. the cash.
and kill all the witnesses.

570
00:39:51.639 --> 00:39:54.682
Then they get Fusco to frame up guys
like Lawrence Pope for murder.

571
00:39:54.892 --> 00:39:56.101
Exactly.

572
00:39:56.602 --> 00:39:58.812
They've already killed five people.

573
00:39:59.021 --> 00:40:01.231
- Six.
- What?

574
00:40:01.982 --> 00:40:04.692
Lawrence Pope was stabbed to death
last night in his cell.

575
00:40:04.902 --> 00:40:07.153
They're trying to cover their tracks.

576
00:40:07.363 --> 00:40:10.907
They couldn't pull this off without
someone on the inside at the DA's office.

577
00:40:11.117 --> 00:40:15.620
That's Wheeler. He's been spying on
Hansen and pulling their old case files.

578
00:40:15.830 --> 00:40:17.705
Including the one for Robinson.

579
00:40:17.915 --> 00:40:21.376
The same Robinson that sent Wheeler
and Hansen death threats from prison.

580
00:40:21.585 --> 00:40:25.004
They looking for someone
they can frame like they framed Pope?

581
00:40:25.214 --> 00:40:27.966
No. I think they found him.
But what do we do?

582
00:40:29.552 --> 00:40:31.177
We stop them.

583
00:40:38.644 --> 00:40:40.228
STILLS [OVER PHONE]:
You wanted to meet?

584
00:40:40.438 --> 00:40:44.190
Remsen and Avenue D
in Canarsie. 20 minutes.

585
00:40:45.776 --> 00:40:48.278
Finch. it's happening now.

586
00:40:58.581 --> 00:41:00.165
HANSEN:
Hello?

587
00:41:06.547 --> 00:41:08.006
Are you here?

588
00:41:12.011 --> 00:41:16.014
Hello?

589
00:41:24.315 --> 00:41:26.816
You're gonna keep me waiting?
We don't have time.

590
00:41:27.026 --> 00:41:29.777
What's your problem? Pope is dead.

591
00:41:30.070 --> 00:41:33.531
His brother is gone. and we're still
searching for the clown who took him.

592
00:41:33.741 --> 00:41:37.494
The problem is Wheeler. you idiot.
He knows.

593
00:41:37.703 --> 00:41:40.163
He knows about Pope
and maybe some of the others.

594
00:41:40.372 --> 00:41:43.082
We should have taken care of
this guy weeks ago.

595
00:41:43.292 --> 00:41:45.460
I even found a shooter for you.

596
00:41:45.669 --> 00:41:48.129
- Stop dragging your feet on this.
- How long do we have?

597
00:41:48.339 --> 00:41:51.716
Twenty-four to 48 hours
before he goes to the DA. tops.

598
00:41:51.926 --> 00:41:55.303
I can take care of the files at the office.
Take care of Wheeler. Tonight.

599
00:42:01.310 --> 00:42:02.685
FUSCO:
Hey. look what I found.

600
00:42:04.730 --> 00:42:06.189
We've got ourselves a groupie.

601
00:42:08.317 --> 00:42:10.360
Heavily armed too.

602
00:42:13.489 --> 00:42:14.864
- You know this guy?
- No.

603
00:42:16.742 --> 00:42:18.034
You're not law enforcement.

604
00:42:18.244 --> 00:42:19.869
Cartel finally grow some stones?

605
00:42:22.373 --> 00:42:23.456
Who the hell are you?

606
00:42:24.542 --> 00:42:27.669
Concerned third party? Ha. ha.

607
00:42:30.589 --> 00:42:34.133
He's alone. that's what he is.
so he doesn't matter.

608
00:42:34.343 --> 00:42:37.136
Take care of him.
And. uh. get rid of Wheeler tonight.

609
00:42:37.346 --> 00:42:39.013
Make it look clean.

610
00:42:39.431 --> 00:42:43.017
Hey. Stills. You screw this up.
I won't let it get to me.

611
00:42:43.227 --> 00:42:45.687
I'll take care of you
just like I took care of Pope.

612
00:42:45.896 --> 00:42:48.565
I can look after myself.
You know that.

613
00:43:13.841 --> 00:43:17.552
- Nice spot.
- It's Oyster Bay.

614
00:43:18.137 --> 00:43:19.971
Glad you like it.

615
00:43:20.180 --> 00:43:22.056
You're gonna be here
a long. long time.

616
00:43:23.726 --> 00:43:25.768
I'm curious...

617
00:43:26.312 --> 00:43:29.230
...was there a point where you knew
you'd become a bad guy?

618
00:43:30.190 --> 00:43:32.609
I got a mortgage to pay.
same as everybody else.

619
00:43:32.943 --> 00:43:35.403
I woke up one day
and I realized I gotta guard...

620
00:43:35.613 --> 00:43:38.072
...these assholes on Wall Street
robbing everybody.

621
00:43:38.282 --> 00:43:41.242
Stealing more than my annual salary
in an afternoon.

622
00:43:42.077 --> 00:43:44.078
So I said. what the hell?

623
00:43:45.998 --> 00:43:48.041
I don't believe you.

624
00:43:49.084 --> 00:43:50.960
See. I've been watching you. Lionel...

625
00:43:51.337 --> 00:43:55.340
...and I think there's a big difference
between you and your friends.

626
00:43:55.549 --> 00:43:57.216
Your heart's not really into it.

627
00:43:58.385 --> 00:44:02.013
Stills. he does it for money. But I think
you do it because you're loyal.

628
00:44:03.682 --> 00:44:04.807
What's the difference?

629
00:44:06.435 --> 00:44:08.311
It's why I'm gonna let you live.

630
00:44:08.771 --> 00:44:10.271
[LAUGHING]

631
00:44:13.942 --> 00:44:15.568
[BOTH LAUGHING]

632
00:44:17.029 --> 00:44:20.990
Yeah. I'm considering sticking
around New York for a while.

633
00:44:21.200 --> 00:44:24.535
If I do. I'm gonna need someone
on the inside.

634
00:44:24.745 --> 00:44:26.537
And you might come in handy.

635
00:44:26.747 --> 00:44:29.916
- So I'm working for you now?
- That's right.

636
00:44:30.376 --> 00:44:31.876
But I've got two rules.

637
00:44:32.419 --> 00:44:36.923
One. you so much as hurt anybody.
and I'll kill you.

638
00:44:37.132 --> 00:44:40.551
I don't particularly like killing people.
but I'm very good at it.

639
00:44:41.720 --> 00:44:45.640
And two. you have to be more careful.

640
00:44:45.849 --> 00:44:48.851
For instance. if you're gonna
put someone in your car...

641
00:44:49.061 --> 00:44:51.479
...you have to search them properly.

642
00:44:53.023 --> 00:44:54.399
What the...?

643
00:45:09.790 --> 00:45:11.040
[GRUNTS]

644
00:45:26.724 --> 00:45:28.224
[SHOUTING]

645
00:45:31.687 --> 00:45:32.937
FUSCO:
What are you doing?

646
00:45:42.281 --> 00:45:44.824
You have your vest on. officer?

647
00:45:45.284 --> 00:45:46.325
Yeah.

648
00:45:51.915 --> 00:45:53.624
[FUSCO GROANING]

649
00:46:08.682 --> 00:46:10.016
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

650
00:46:11.310 --> 00:46:13.227
- Where the hell have...?
REESE: There's no time.

651
00:46:13.437 --> 00:46:15.313
We were wrong.
Hansen isn't the target.

652
00:46:15.522 --> 00:46:17.899
She's the ringleader.
They're going after Wheeler.

653
00:46:18.108 --> 00:46:19.817
Tonight.

654
00:46:26.200 --> 00:46:27.575
[TIRES SQUEALING]

655
00:46:36.502 --> 00:46:39.420
Yo. Wheeler's up there.

656
00:46:39.630 --> 00:46:42.465
He heads to the gym most nights.
I got Doyle upstairs.

657
00:46:42.674 --> 00:46:45.843
Place is a dump. There's no doorman.
no cameras. nobody.

658
00:46:46.053 --> 00:46:49.722
We'll take him in the lobby. Soon
as it's done. we take the shooter out.

659
00:46:49.932 --> 00:46:53.059
Give him a block. take him out.
Head shots this time. understand?

660
00:46:53.268 --> 00:46:56.437
- Yeah. yeah.
- Get our friend out of the trunk.

661
00:46:57.564 --> 00:47:01.275
- Who is this guy?
STILLS: Some ex-con Wheeler put away.

662
00:47:10.244 --> 00:47:12.370
Azarello. lights.

663
00:47:17.459 --> 00:47:20.336
- Doyle. talk to me.
- He's coming out now.

664
00:47:25.342 --> 00:47:26.551
Come on. Henry. let's go.

665
00:47:26.760 --> 00:47:28.511
- Wait.
- Remember that basketball game...

666
00:47:28.720 --> 00:47:31.347
...we're supposed to go to?
- He's got his kid with him.

667
00:47:31.557 --> 00:47:32.849
What a waste.

668
00:47:33.475 --> 00:47:35.184
WHEELER:
Better watch out.

669
00:47:42.442 --> 00:47:44.902
You're a very bad man. Charles.

670
00:47:45.112 --> 00:47:49.740
You're about to kill a man.
And his son.

671
00:47:54.079 --> 00:47:56.539
Please. Please don't do this.

672
00:47:58.125 --> 00:48:00.084
Drop your weapon.

673
00:48:19.730 --> 00:48:21.272
WHEELER:
I think that's true. actually.

674
00:48:21.481 --> 00:48:24.734
You keep working on it.
you'll be able to throw that fast.

675
00:48:24.943 --> 00:48:26.485
- Really?
- Absolutely.

676
00:48:49.217 --> 00:48:50.426
Let him go.

677
00:48:51.136 --> 00:48:52.887
I can't do that.

678
00:48:53.096 --> 00:48:55.139
I let him go.
my friends and I go to jail.

679
00:48:56.433 --> 00:48:57.516
[SHOUTS]

680
00:48:59.978 --> 00:49:06.108
Drag your friend outside
and take him to the hospital. Right now.

681
00:49:11.657 --> 00:49:13.866
I think I kill you and your friend here.

682
00:49:14.076 --> 00:49:16.243
Make it look like you killed each other.

683
00:49:16.453 --> 00:49:19.872
Then. just because
you pissed me off...

684
00:49:20.082 --> 00:49:24.293
...I'm going to kill your family.
and all your friends.

685
00:49:25.170 --> 00:49:29.340
I don't have any friends.
I don't have any family left. either.

686
00:49:30.926 --> 00:49:32.176
Left them all behind.

687
00:49:33.178 --> 00:49:35.513
Went around the world
looking for bad guys.

688
00:49:36.223 --> 00:49:38.849
But there were plenty of you.
right here. all along.

689
00:49:41.728 --> 00:49:43.396
[GUNFIRE]

690
00:49:48.652 --> 00:49:50.027
[CHATTERING ON MONITOR]

691
00:49:56.326 --> 00:49:59.078
ATTORNEY: So now. essentially.
you're telling us you couldn't see...

692
00:49:59.287 --> 00:50:02.331
...what was happening
in the parking lot at all.

693
00:50:03.166 --> 00:50:06.168
- I'm done. Your Honor.
SMITH: Ms. Hansen?

694
00:50:06.378 --> 00:50:10.381
The state isn't paying you by the hour.
counselor.

695
00:50:11.258 --> 00:50:14.301
Why don't we have the defendant
tell you in her own words?

696
00:50:14.511 --> 00:50:16.887
Let's listen to the 911 call she made.

697
00:50:19.474 --> 00:50:22.184
HANSEN [ON RECORDING]:
And. hey. take care of Wheeler. tonight.

698
00:50:22.394 --> 00:50:26.480
Make it look clean. Stills.
you screw this up. I won't let it get to me.

699
00:50:26.690 --> 00:50:29.358
I'll take care of you
just like I took care of Pope.

700
00:50:29.568 --> 00:50:32.403
I can look after myself. You know that.

701
00:50:49.254 --> 00:50:50.671
[GRUNTS]

702
00:50:52.966 --> 00:50:54.258
[GROANS]

703
00:50:55.260 --> 00:50:57.928
You ready to get to work. officer?

704
00:50:59.389 --> 00:51:01.515
I'm no good to you. I'm dead.

705
00:51:01.725 --> 00:51:04.226
Just a matter of time
before the gangs get me.

706
00:51:04.436 --> 00:51:07.480
- Or IA.
- No one knows you're involved.

707
00:51:07.689 --> 00:51:08.981
I took care of that.

708
00:51:09.191 --> 00:51:12.026
Besides. they'll be too busy
looking for Stills.

709
00:51:12.235 --> 00:51:14.820
The police'll think he's run for it.

710
00:51:15.030 --> 00:51:17.990
The gangs and the mob
will think he's gone Witness Protection.

711
00:51:18.200 --> 00:51:21.160
- Is that where he is. Witness Protection?
- No. Lionel.

712
00:51:21.369 --> 00:51:23.370
He's in the trunk.

713
00:51:24.122 --> 00:51:27.166
I gave him a choice and he chose wrong.

714
00:51:27.834 --> 00:51:33.631
Only problem is. uh.
well. I had to shoot him with your gun.

715
00:51:33.840 --> 00:51:36.092
You'd have a hard time
explaining that one.

716
00:51:36.301 --> 00:51:39.595
So. ha. ha.
you'll be taking another trip.

717
00:51:39.805 --> 00:51:42.640
But I'm not coming along this time.

718
00:51:46.436 --> 00:51:49.105
- Where am I going?
- Oyster Bay.

719
00:51:49.314 --> 00:51:53.651
Where no one's gonna find him
for a long. long time.

720
00:51:54.277 --> 00:51:55.319
I'll be in touch.

721
00:51:55.529 --> 00:51:56.904
[CHUCKLES]

722
00:52:13.672 --> 00:52:15.297
You have a decision to make.

723
00:52:16.007 --> 00:52:18.467
The machine gave you
another number.

724
00:52:18.677 --> 00:52:21.178
The numbers never stop coming.

725
00:52:21.388 --> 00:52:23.806
You should know that up front.

726
00:52:24.057 --> 00:52:25.975
Two questions.

727
00:52:26.184 --> 00:52:27.852
First...

728
00:52:28.061 --> 00:52:29.145
...why me?

729
00:52:30.105 --> 00:52:33.941
I've been watching you
for a long time. John.

730
00:52:34.734 --> 00:52:37.153
We have more in common
than you might think.

731
00:52:37.362 --> 00:52:40.781
The world thinks we're both dead.
for starters.

732
00:52:44.369 --> 00:52:45.911
You said two questions.

733
00:52:48.290 --> 00:52:51.876
You programmed the machine
to delete those irrelevant numbers.

734
00:52:52.085 --> 00:52:54.295
But now you're trying to save them.

735
00:52:55.046 --> 00:52:56.172
What changed your mind?

736
00:52:56.882 --> 00:53:00.718
Let's just say you're not the only one
that's lost someone.

737
00:53:03.221 --> 00:53:06.640
If you wanna leave. I'll give you
enough money to get as far as you need.

738
00:53:06.933 --> 00:53:08.684
Disappear.

739
00:53:10.187 --> 00:53:11.812
And if I stay?

740
00:53:13.064 --> 00:53:15.316
They'll come looking for you.

741
00:53:16.193 --> 00:53:19.153
The police. the mob.
your old friends at the CIA.

742
00:53:20.572 --> 00:53:23.657
If you stay and we continue to do this...

743
00:53:25.076 --> 00:53:28.829
...sooner or later.
both of us will probably wind up dead.

744
00:53:30.207 --> 00:53:33.375
Actually dead. this time.

745
00:53:36.463 --> 00:53:38.714
I said I'd tell you the truth.

746
00:53:40.383 --> 00:53:42.343
I didn't say you'd like it.

747
00:53:50.310 --> 00:53:53.354
CARTER: Start talking. officer.
- You think I'm gonna rat on my friends?

748
00:53:53.563 --> 00:53:56.190
Please. you can tell the DA
all about your crooked pals.

749
00:53:56.399 --> 00:53:58.817
I wanna know about him.
the guy who came after you.

750
00:53:59.027 --> 00:54:02.154
I don't know anything.
He was just some guy alone. In a suit.

751
00:54:02.364 --> 00:54:05.157
You're gonna tell me everything
you don't know about him...

752
00:54:05.367 --> 00:54:07.326
...and where I can find him.

753
00:54:48.994 --> 00:54:50.744
[CHATTERING ON MONITOR]

754
00:55:44.424 --> 00:55:46.425
[English - US - SDH]
